Fans installed within ceiling areas are in the correct location as per Mechanical Drawings
Fans Installed correctly with rubber isolation pads
All Flex has been run to correct location
All flex are hung independent of other services and supported by intact load spreaders
Butterfly dampers are installed on the PODs grille neck and they are in a fully opened position and air tight sealed
Flatpack duct is installed as per approved mechanical shop drawings
Internal side of flatpack duct and fittings are clear from debris and dust
Is flatpack supported from ceiling using metal hangers or metal support clips at every 2m intervals so that the flatpacks are not sagging?
Wherever the flatpacks are screwed into, ensure properly sealed
Flatpack joints & fittings are properly sealed.
Are correct type of fittings used?
